OL,3,CBlack people in UK 'almost four times
OL,4,Cmore likely to become homeless'
OL,6,FA three-and-a-half-year study by the
OL,7,FInstitute for Social Policy, Housing,
OL,8,FEqualities Research (I-SPHERE) at
OL,9,FHeriot-Watt University analysed
OL,10,F750,000 household records and found
OL,11,Fthat just 10% of Black families
OL,12,Fsecured social housing through the
OL,13,Fhomelessness system, compared to 24%
OL,14,Fof White families.
OL,16,FAs part of the study, black people
OL,17,Faffected by housing discrimination
OL,18,Fwere interviewed, with many saying
OL,19,Fthey felt the need to mask their
OL,20,Fidentities - a common theme that
OL,21,Femerged across focus groups.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/13
